   reduced when the implied beat was at a slower tempo (1,500 ms) than when
   it was at a faster tempo (600 ms). Decreased beat induction was
   accompanied by decreased functional activity in the basal ganglia,
   premotor and supplementary motor regions, and thalamus. Findings support
   the conclusion that rhythms presented at a slow tempo reduce involvement
