Abstract = {{In the present functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI) study, we
   investigated the role of different brain regions in separate aspects of
   mentalizing. Young females aged 18-19 years were asked to imagine a
   social situation and answer a question. Perspective, self and other, as
   well as content, emotion, and behavior, were varied. Activation was
   observed in the left precuneus, left temporoparietal junction, left
   medial prefrontal cortex and left middle temporal gyrus. Left precuneus
   and left temporoparietal junction were recruited more when taking the
   perspective of other than when taking the perspective of self. Medial
   prefrontal areas might be more involved during mentalizing about emotion
   versus baseline than about behavior versus baseline.}},
